<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mantilla Wins Bologna Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Felix Mantilla of Spain came from a
set down to win from French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten in the
final of the Bologna clay-court tennis tournament in Bologna on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Mantilla ended the Brazilian's winning streak of 16
matches. Ranked 16th, he triumphed 4-6, 6-2, 6-1 in sweltering
heat to earn his second ATP title.
</P>
<P>
A wild card entry to the Bologna tournament, Mantilla pounced
on a string of errors by his Brazilian opponent, who was seeded
eighth.
</P>
<P>
20-year-old Kuerten appeared well below his recent form.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
