<HEADLINE> Netherlands Wins Four-nation Men's Field Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Netherlands defeated Pakistan 4-0
in its third and final match to win the title at the Rabobank
International Trophy four-nation men's field hockey tournament in
Amstelveen, Netherlands on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Netherlands recorded all three victories and collected nine
points for the champion.
</P>
<P>
In another match, England drew with South Africa 2-2 and took
the second place with one win, one draw and one defeat.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan had one win and two defeats for the third place while
South Africa was the fourth with one draw and two defeats.
</P>
</TEXT>
