<HEADLINE> German Bolts Wins Dauphine Libere Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Udo Bolts of Germany won the crown
for the Dauphine Libere cycling race that finished at Chambery,
France, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He made up a deficit of one minute and nine seconds to beat
overnight leader Abraham Olano of Spain into second place by 12
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Andrei Teteriuk of Kazakhstan won the seventh and last stage
over 182 kilometers from Briancon to Chambery.
</P>
<P>
Olano, seeking a third successive Spanish win after Miguel
Indurain in 1995 and 1996, suffered a fall, a puncture and
technical problems in the final hour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
