<HEADLINE> US Defense Secretary Arrives in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 15 (Xinhua) -- U.S. States Defense Secretary
William Cohen arrived here today from Saudi Arabia for a two-day
visit to boost bilateral military relations.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at the Kuwaiti International Airport by Deputy
Prime Minister and Defense Minister Sheikh Salem and other Senior
officials.
</P>
<P>
Cohen will hold talks with his Kuwaiti counterpart on a number
of defense issues, the Kuwait News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Cohen, while in Saudi Arabia, reaffirmed the U.S. commitment to
security of the world top oil producer and exporter. His talks
with Saudi leaders also tackled means of boosting security and
stability in the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Salem said Saturday Cohen's visit came within the
framework of bolstering the Kuwaiti-U.S. ties and common
understanding in the defense field.
</P>
<P>
He said Cohen's visit to Kuwait is a continuation of "the
common cooperation march," and it was to "study all developments
at both international and regional levels, in particular what
concerns Kuwait and the Gulf Cooperation Council affairs, the
exchange of expertise in the military field and bolstering
bilateral ties." 
