<HEADLINE> Iraq Says Palestine is An Arab Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein
here today reiterated his country's position towards the
Palestinian issue, emphasizing that Palestine is an Arab country,
</P>
<P>
According to the Iraqi News Agency, Saddam said at a cabinet
meeting today that Iraq's position towards the Palestinian issue
was, is still and will be as it is: Palestine is an Arab country.
</P>
<P>
This statement came after the U.S. Congress made a decision to
move the U.S. embassy in Israel from Tel Aviv to al-Quds
(Jerusalem).
</P>
<P>
The U.S. House of Representatives passed a non-binding
resolution Tuesday recognizing as Israel's "undivided capital" and
earmarking 100 million dollars to move U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv
to Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi president said that Iraq "is ready, in accordance
with its national responsibilities, to discuss with other Arab
countries the matters on the basis of this prospective,
irrespective of the backgrounds and details of the past."
</P>
<P>
The timing and nature of the U.S. Congress' decision prove
that the U.S. does not play a balanced role in the Arab-Israel
conflict "when the matter is related to Israel's calculations and
those of the U.S. itself," Saddam stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi cabinet said that some states have taken al-Quads as
headquarters for their embassies, which it described as "a
challenge to Arab feelings and the rights of the Palestinians,
Arab and Islamic nations."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
