<HEADLINE> France Again Denies Rumored Arms Sale to Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- France today again denied a report
by a Taiwan newspaper that a French company is selling 2,000
anti-tank missiles to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the French Foreign Ministry said that France
sticks to the 1994 Sino-French Joint Communique, in which Paris
promised not to sell any more armaments to Taiwan from then on.
</P>
<P>
"The policy (of France) is defined by the Franco-Chinese
agreement of 1994," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
France denied on Wednesday another report by the same Taiwan
newspaper, the China Times, that the Socialist government of
France was considering selling 60 Mirage 2000-5 combat aircraft to
Taiwan.
</P>
