A former Socialist government of France sold 60 Mirage 2000-5
fighters to Taiwan in 1993, an action which greatly harmed the
Sino-French relations.
</P>
<P>
When President Jacques Chirac visited China in May, the French
government reaffirmed its commitment not to sell armaments to
Taiwan. 
