<HEADLINE> Twelve Romanians Killed in Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people have been killed
in a storm-caused flood that occurred in northwestern Romania on
Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains in Bihor country late on Saturday caused the
Barcau River to rise sharply and break through the bank. Five
bridges were destroyed and seven townships inundated.
</P>
<P>
This is the worst flood in the region since 1970. The
government has sent officials to the affected area to organize
rescue operations. 
