<HEADLINE> Sino-Foreign Joint Semiconductor Maker Gains QS 9000 Certification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Advanced Semiconductor
Manufacturing Corp. of Shanghai, a Sino-foreign venture, today was
given the international certification of QS 9000, and is believed
to be the first hi-tech company in China to get the accreditation
for its high-grade products.
</P>
<P>
QS 9000, which is a quality standard jointly issued by three
US-based big-name automobile manufacturers, Chrysler, Ford and
General Motors, has higher qualification requirements than the
standard ISO 9000.
</P>
<P>
The accreditation is expected to help satisfy overseas
customers with products made in China with Chinese parts, and also
is expected to help the company increase its exports to overseas
markets.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of 200 million US dollars, the company, jointly
operated by China, Holland, and Canada, now has two integrated
circuit chip production lines, to produce 17,000 five-inch chips
and 15,000 six-inch chips per month.
</P>
<P>
In addition to domestic markets, the company exports a majority
of its products to American and European countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
