<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Members of HKSAR Provisional District Organizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa has decided
that all existing members of the Urban Council, the Regional
Council and the 18 District Boards will continue to serve on the
Provincial Urban Council, the Provisional Regional Council and the
Provisional District Boards respectively.
</P>
<P>
When announcing this here today, a spokesman of the Chief
Executive Office said the Urban (Amendment) Bill 1997 and the
Regional Council (Amendment) Bill 1997 stated that the Provisional
Urban Council and the Provisional Regional Council would each have
no more than 50 members.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, no more than nine and no more than 11 additional
members can be appointed to the Provisional Urban Council and the
Provisional Regional Council respectively.
</P>
<P>
And the District Boards (Amendment) Bill 1997 stated that the
18 Provisional District Boards would each have no more than 40
members, and, therefore, the additional appointments to each
Provisional District Board vary from three to eight, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
The Urban Council (Amendment) Bill 1997 and the Regional
Council (Amendment) Bill 1997 had their third readings by the
Provisional Legislative Council on June 7. They will be enacted
when the Chief Executive gives his assent on July 1.
</P>
<P>
These persons were drawn from different professions and sectors
of the community, and were selected on their merits, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that, with their expertise and experience,
these people will be able to contribute meaningfully to the work
of the two provisional councils and the Provisional District
Boards," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
