<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Visits Kyrkyzstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BESHKENT, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian, who arrived here today for a five-day visit, held talks
with his Kyrkyz counterpart Myrzakan Subanov on bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
The two men believed in their talks that bilateral cooperation
in political, economic and military fields is not only in the
interests of the two countries but also conducive to regional and
global peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Subanov said that developing relations with China is a top
priority of his country's foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the military confidence building treaty and the
troop reduction agreement signed by China, Kazakhstan, Kyrkyzstan,
Russia and Tajikistan in the past two years have laid a solid
foundation for his country to develop relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Chi said China highly values its relations with Kyrkyzstan and
appreciates Kyrkyzstan's stance on Taiwan, Tibet and other issues.
</P>
<P>
Describing the allegation of so-called "China threat" as
groundless, Chi said that China's defense policy is purely
defensive.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that China will never seek hegemony, nor will it
join any military blocs or establish any overseas military bases.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese general is on the last leg of his four-nation tour
of the former Soviet republics. He had visited Belarus, Ukraine
and Kazakhstan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
