<HEADLINE> H.K.-Beijing Paragliding Meet in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong to Beijing motorised
paragliding rally will start on Septebmer 7 on Monday, organizers
said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Paragliders will take off from Hong Kong and fly over the
provinces of Guangdong, Hunan, Hubei, Hebei and Henan in 16 legs,
they said.
</P>
<P>
The competitors will arrive at the foot of the Great Wall in
suburban Beijing after the 3,000-kilometer journey.
</P>
<P>
The motorised paraglide is a parachute-like glide powered by a
small engine with propellers.
</P>
<P>
The aviation sport, introduced into China in early 1990s, is
developing quickly in the country along with its unmotorised
cousin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
