</P>
<P>
-- European Union leaders gather in Amsterdam for a two-day
summit with their plan to launch a common currency in 1999 still
hanging in the balance.
</P>
<P>
-- Consumer spending ahead of a tax increase pushed the
Japanese economy to unexpected heights in the first quarter, but a
full-fledged recovery for the remainder of the year isn't very
likely. 
