<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Leading Bank Optimistic About Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking
Corporation Ltd. president John Strickland said here today that he
is optimistic about the prospect of Shanghai as a world center of
finance.
</P>
<P>
He said that Shanghai has played an important role in promoting
economic development in China's coastal regions, and China must
accept as reality that in the near future, Shanghai will become as
important a world financial center as Hong Kong is today.
</P>
<P>
The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Ltd. has been
operating in Shanghai since its establishment in 1856 in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, the bank has provided financial services
to more than 2,000 projects across China, including the
construction of the Nanpu Bridge and Yangpu Bridge in Shanghai,
Strickland said.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident about the economic development in Shanghai
and our businesses here will be limitless," he said at an opening
ceremony today of a new business center in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The bank was among the first group of overseas banks allowed to
do the yuan-based business as of December last year. 
