<HEADLINE> Beijing to Hold Celebrations for Return of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Large-scale celebrations and a
rally will be held in Beijing on June 30 and July 1 to mark the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland, official sources announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
"The Evening Party of Beijing People Greeting the Return of
Hong Kong to the Motherland" on June 30 will be held in Tiananmen
Square with 100,000 attendants, and will last throughout the night
until the ceremonial raising of the national flag on the square
the next day.
</P>
<P>
The Press and Propaganda Office Celebrating the Return of Hong
Kong and the Beijing Press Center unveiled the details of the gala
at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Giant television screens will be mounted on the square so that
the crowd can watch live television broadcasts of the handover
ceremony in Hong Kong at midnight. Fireworks will be included in
the celebrations.
</P>
<P>
A symphonic and dance performance titled "Beijing Bless You --
Hong Kong" and many other shows also will be staged.
</P>
<P>
"The Grand Rally of the Capital Celebrating the Return of Hong
Kong to the Motherland" will be convened in the evening in the
Beijing Workers' Stadium, in which the audience will be
entertained with song and dance performances.
</P>
<P>
All the major celebrations events will be telecast live
throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
During the period of June 28 to July 3, the capital city will
be lighted at night, and decorated with flowers, colorful flags,
and lanterns. 
