<HEADLINE> Funeral of Noted Beijing Opera Artist Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Funeral services for Zhang Junqiu,
a noted Beijing Opera star and drama instructor, were held today
at the Babaoshan Revolutionary Cemetery in western Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Zhang died of illness on May 27. He was 77.
</P>
<P>
Among those who paid their last respects to the artist were
Qiao Shi and Li Ruihuan, Standing Committee members of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC); Ding Guangen, head of the Propaganda Department of
the CPC Central Committee, and State Councillor Li Tieying.
</P>
<P>
Wreaths in the mourning hall were sent in the name of Party and
state leaders including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li
Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren.
</P>
<P>
Born in Beijing in 1920, Zhang first studied Beijing Opera at
the age of 13. He was best known for combined traditional music
with voices in innovative ways. Zhang was the founder of the
School of Zhang in Beijing Opera.
</P>
<P>
Zhang once was a member of the Standing Committee of the Eighth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, vice-chairman of China Federation of Literary and Art
Circles and advisor of the China Drama Academy.
</P>
<P>
He became a CPC member at age 61.  
</P>
</TEXT>
