<HEADLINE> EU to Organize Energy Workshop With Partner Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
European Union (EU)'s executive body, will organize a workshop in
Brussels on Tuesday and Wednesday within the framework of the
Euro-Mediterranean Energy Forum.
</P>
<P>
The forum, which links the EU with 12 northern African and
Middle East countries, held its first meeting in Brussels on May
13, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is designed to identify options to facilitate
energy investments in the partner countries, said a press release
issued here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The main issues to be addressed at the workshop will include
energy efficiency and renewable energy in market economy
conditions, major risks and barriers for private sector
investments in the partner countries and recommended policies for
capital mobilization.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will bring together senior officials from the
partner countries and EU member states as well as the
representatives of the European Investment Bank, the World Bank
and the Energy Charter Secretariat. 
