<HEADLINE> Flourishing Chinese City Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The flourishing city of Sanming
in southeast China's Fujian Province has succeeded in attracting
173 million US dollars of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
At a business fair held today in Shenzhen, one of China's
special economic zones, overseas investors signed contracts to
fund 65 projects in the city, located in northwest Fujian.
</P>
<P>
The investors mainly came from Japan, the United States,
France, and Hong Kong and Taiwan regions. The projects are related
to industry, agriculture, energy, transport, real estate and
tourism, according to Mayor of Sanming city.
</P>
<P>
The biggest project is a thermal power plant involving an
investment of 56.7 million US dollars from a Hong Kong company.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the local GDP of Sanming, which has a population of
2.58 million, reached 20.074 billion yuan (about 2.42 billion US
dollars), and 80.27 million US dollars of overseas investment were
injected into the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
