<HEADLINE> ROK Involves in Shanghai's Mobile Telecom Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd. from
the Republic of Korea (ROK) today signed a contract with Shanghai
Great Wall Mobile Communication Co. Ltd. to jointly develop a new
commercial mobile telecom network in Shanghai, China's economic
and financial center.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to create a new digital mobile telecom
system based on the technical standard called coded division
multi-addresses (CDMA).
</P>
<P>
Telecom experts said that the new system could ensure clear
sound quality similar to that of wired telephones. And compared
with the analogue mobile telecom network of the same capacity, the
CDMA nets require fewer base stations to cover the same area, thus
reducing the cost.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, the first-phase of construction will
include one main switch and 67 base stations which can cover all
of Shanghai. Upon completion early next year, the net can provide
service for 60,000 users. 
</P>
</TEXT>
