<HEADLINE> 17 Military Personnel Missing In East Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen military personnel were
missing Sunday in Eastern Province of Sri Lanka, according to
military sources today.
</P>
<P>
Government forces are still searching for the missing including
11 air force personnel.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the air force group was on a patrol when they
encountered a group of Tamil rebels in the Amparai area and
fighting lasted for nearly four hours.
</P>
<P>
The rebels suffered heavy casualties. A search operation is
going on and there had been no report of the missing personnel,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year guerrilla war for
a separate state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
