<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 4.58 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market lost 4.58 points to 4025.41
today as against last Friday's close of 4029.99.
</P>
<P>
The National Index also eased by 1.44 points to 1725.27 from
1726.71 previously.
</P>
<P>
The BSE Sensitive Index started better at 4043.2 and shot up to
the intra-day high of 4076.56. However, heavy selling pressure
forced the index to fall to 4006.8 before closing at 4025.41.
</P>
<P>
A sharp decline in the shares of ITC held back the continued
surge in the Sensitive Index in spite of further upswings in some
other front-line scrip on the BSE market today in the wake of
panic selling by local operators and profit-taking by financial
institutions.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said the market was in a overbought position and a
technical correction is necessary for a healthy market.  
</P>
