<HEADLINE> Malaysian Business Confident of HK's Bright Prospects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian business circle
is confident of the future of Hong Kong after its return to China
on July 1, 1997, believing view that Hong Kong will continue to be
stable and prosperous.
</P>
<P>
"It is my firm belief that Hong Kong after its return to China
will continue to prosper and progress and will play a greater role
in promoting economic and trade cooperation between Malaysia and
China,"
President of the Associated Chinese Chambers of Commerce and
Industry of Malaysia (ACCCIM) Wee Boon Ping said in a recent
exclusive interview with Xinhua here.
</P>
<P>
Wee noted that the position of Hong Kong as an international
financial and trade center would not be affected because of
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong,
rather it would be strengthened because of China's backing.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong would continue to prosper because it is the
wish of the Chinese government and people as well as the wish of
overseas Chinese businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Wee added that the ACCCIM, the top leading body of Chinese
businessmen in Malaysia with tens of thousands of members, will
continue to use Hong Kong as its business base for future business
expansion.
</P>
<P>
In a separate exclusive interview with Xinhua here recently,
President of the Sino-Malaysian Chambers of Commerce and Economy
Ngan Ching Wen said, "I am optimistic about the future of Hong
Kong."
</P>
<P>
With the policies laid down by the Chinese government to be
implemented in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Hong
Kong will "surely continue to remain prosperous and stable, to
display its economic vigor and to maintain its position as a world
economic center," Ngan said.
</P>
<P>
Yeoh Tiong Lay, another renowned businessman in Malaysia, also
expressed his belief that the future of Hong Kong after its return
to China would be better as it would have closer links with the
inland areas of China.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his confidence in Hong Kong's future, the executive
chairman of YTL Corporation Berhad (Limited) said in a recent
interview with Xinhua here that Hong Kong would be "more
prosperous" and would have a "better tomorrow" in view of its
closer links with the inland areas and the "one country, two
systems" administrative mechanism.
</P>
<P>
Yeoh said the fact that investors now return to Hong Kong for
investment shows that they are confident of the future of Hong
Kong and the upward trend on the Hong Kong stock market is also an
indicator that the Hong Kong people have confidence in the future
of the territory.
</P>
<P>
He said his corporation would continue to use Hong Kong as a
gateway to expand its business in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
