<HEADLINE> Jansher Threatens to Boycott Pakistan Open Squash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Squash world champion Jansher Khan
said on Monday he would boycott the Pakistan Open in Karachi in
August unless the Pakistani federation attracted more publicity
about squash events played in the country.
</P>
<P>
Jansher said in Cairo, where he is competing in the al-Ahram
international squash championship, that television coverage was
the best way to popularise the game in Pakistan, especially among
young people.
</P>
<P>
The world champion said the sport was gaining ground in Egypt
because of the media coverage of teenaged local hero Ahmed Barada,
now ranked fifth in the world and one of the semi-finalists in the
al-Ahram championship.
</P>
<P>
"I am the best in the world. Pakistan must take advantage of
that and until the (Pakistan Squash) Federation takes action in
the direction I will not play in another Pakistan Open," Jansher
added.
</P>
<P>
"If we do not do something now about promoting our success in
squash, Pakistan will lose the leadership of the game," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
