<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Journalists to Investigate, Report on the Poor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- One hundred Chinese journalists
went on assignment today to some of the country's poorest areas,
charged with investigating and reporting on the psychological
outlook of the local people.
</P>
<P>
Following a send-off ceremony here, the journalists headed off
in groups to southwest China's Guizhou, Sichuan and Yunnan
provinces, northwest China's Shaanxi Province and the Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region, and central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The activity was organized by the All-China Journalist
Association (ACJA), an office in charge of poverty alleviation
under the State Council, and the Foundation for Poverty
Alleviation in China.
</P>
<P>
ACJA chairman Shao Huaze conveyed support to the volunteers
from Ding Guangen, member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and head of the
Propaganda Department of the CPC Central Committee.  
</P>
