<HEADLINE> Iran Has 1,047 AIDS Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Iran has a total of 1,047 AIDS
victims with 70 to 80 percent of them contracting the deadly
disease through sexual contacts, the Iranian health minister said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Alireza Marandi said at a symposium on AIDS
that the rest of the AIDS victims in Iran have been
afflicted by contaminated blood.
</P>
<P>
Ruling out the possibility of blood derivatives and
biological medicines being contaminated in Iran, he said that
such products are under strict control and are free from any
contamination.
</P>
<P>
The symposium on AIDS discussed such topics as the
government's policies of fighting AIDS, the role of morality and
education in preventing the spread of the killer disease, HIV,
AIDS and tuberculosis, AIDS in women and infants, and treatment
of AIDS victims.
</P>
<P>
According to an early report, Iran's Blood Transfusion
Organization (IBTO) has recently decided to offer free
consultation to citizens who might be afraid of having
contracted AIDS disease.
</P>
<P>
IBTO Director Jahangir Ahmadi said that the service was
provided to all and was not in exchange for offering blood
at the IBTO headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
