<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Party Hosts Symposium to Greet HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Peasants' and Workers'
Democratic Party held a symposium here today to greet the return
of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Fang Rongxin, executive vice-chairman of the party, presided
over the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In his keynote speech, Fang said the return of Hong Kong is a
very important event for both China and the world and a mark of
success for Deng Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
It also signals an important step for the reunification of the
motherland, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Peasants' and Workers' Democratic Party has
deep-rooted historical ties with Hong Kong. During the democratic
revolution, Hong Kong twice served as a base for the central
committee of the party, and accumulated precious strength for the
party, he noted.
</P>
<P>
After the founding of the People's Republic of China in 1949,
the Chinese Peasants' and Workers' Democratic Party has created
more links with the Hong Kong compatriots, and encouraged them to
invest in the inland areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fang, who will attend the handover ceremony in Hong Kong with
the delegation of the Chinese government, said he believes Hong
Kong will be more prosperous and stable after the return, and will
have an even brighter future.
</P>
<P>
Also addressing the symposium were Vice-Chairmen of the Party
Song Jinsheng and Jiang Zhenghua and some other party members.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, the participants went to Tiananmen Square
and took photos in front of the countdown board that marks Hong
Kong's return.  
</P>
</TEXT>
