<HEADLINE> Share Prices Almost Unchanged on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply
during the day's trading, but recovered later on the Singapore
market, with the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index ending
at 1991.08 points, up by 0.96 points from last Friday's close.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 157.84 million units,
valued at 334.83 million Singapore dollars (about 234.15 million
U.S. dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 219 to 71 while
340 other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Guthrie GTS was the most actively traded stock as it registered
a turnover of 32.54 million units. It was followed by Australia
Land which had 10.88 million shares traded. Keppel Land warrant 00
was next with 10.05 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 50 cents to finish at 22.1 Singapore
dollars. Car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage increased by 40 cents to
end at 14.3 Singapore dollars while Sea View closed 30 cents
higher at 10.9 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Samanda Holdings was the biggest loser as it
fell by 50 cents to end at 10.7 Singapore dollars. F&AMP;N and GP Bat
declined by 30 cents each to close at 10.2 and 4.32 dollars
respectively. City Developments, the Development Bank of Singapore
(DBS) Foreign, the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC)
Foreign and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign lost 20
cents each to finish at 13.6, 18, 15, and 27.6 Singapore dollars
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
