<HEADLINE> Spartak Official Murdered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Larisa Nechayeva, director general
of the Spartak soccer club in Russia, was shot dead Sunday at her
country home outside Moscow, a soccer club said Monday.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified woman who was a Spartak employee was also
killed by the attackers while Nechayeva's driver was injured.
</P>
<P>
Nechayeva, one of the most famous women executives in Russian
sports, was shot in the head and the chest, club spokesman
Alexander Lvov said Monday.
</P>
<P>
No arrests have been made and police was still investigating
the case.
</P>
<P>
In April, Valentin Sych, president of Russia's Ice Hockey
Federation, was shot and killed at his country house outside
Moscow. The crime was not solved. 
</P>
