<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Japanese Extremists' Landing on Diaoyu Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- China is indignant that Japanese
right-wingers have landed again on China's Diaoyu Islands, Chinese
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Cui Tiankai said here today.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark when asked by a reporter to comment on the
activities of June 11, when three Japanese right-wingers landed on
Beixiao Island attached to Diaoyu Islands.
</P>
<P>
Cui said that the Diaoyu Islands and its attached islands have
been an integral part of the Chinese territory since ancient
times, and China's stand on this issue has been clear and
consistent.
</P>
<P>
"We are indignant at Japanese right-wingers' landing on the
Diaoyu Islands again, which is an illegal action ignoring China's
position and severely infringing upon China's sovereignty," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the Chinese Foreign Ministry has
appealed to the the Japanese government to respect China's stand
and honor its commitment and take measures to stop such events
from happening again, while taking into consideration the general
situation of Sino-Japanese relations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
