<HEADLINE> State Councillor Chen Junsheng Stresses Poverty Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Chen Junsheng
said recently that the hard work of officials at various levels is
key to helping local farmers shed poverty.
</P>
<P>
During his inspection tour from June 10 to 15 in some poor
areas in southwest China's Sichuan Province, Chen said that county
and township officials should visit poor villages and families and
work actively to solve the food and clothing problems of the
masses.
</P>
<P>
Chen, also director of the Leading Group in Charge of Aid-the
Poor Projects under the State Council, noted that to transform the
impoverished areas, priority should be given to improving the
agricultural infrastructure, adding that in addition to grain
production, industries which make use of local resource advantages
should be encouraged such as cultivating fruits, vegetables, and
medicinal herbs. 
</P>
