<HEADLINE> Philippine Stock Market Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Stock Exchange (PSE)
continued to dip today due to lack of foreign investors, with the
30-share composite index down 10.75 points from 2,790.86 points
recorded last Friday.
</P>
<P>
In today's trading, the majority of stock price indices
declined, except the banking and financial services which gained
slightly to reach 916.76 points, or up by 7.93 points, on the
average.
</P>
<P>
The commercial and industrial sector averaged 3,062.10 or down
by 17.45 points, while the property sector posted 1,382.12 or down
by 2.71 points. The mining, oil and all shares indices also
trailed on the downside.
</P>
<P>
Gainers were recorded at 56 while the number of declines was 58
with those unchanged standing at 72.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,5433,360,320 shares were traded with a total value
of 1,082,831,772.10 pesos (41,329,456.951 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Analysts at the PSE Research Department predicted that the
local bourse will likely experience the wrath of a lull in the
coming days as clearly manifested by the weak trading activity
today.
</P>
<P>
In the past few days of trading, the composite index was not
doing properly as investors were waiting for active issues to
upturn, they said.
</P>
<P>
They have apprehensions that the lull may continue within the
week because foreign investors seemed unconcerned or that they
simply pump their investments somewhere else where stock market
issues are considered to be rosy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
