<HEADLINE> Book on Shooting of "Opium War" Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A two volume set of books
detailing the logistics of filming "The Opium War" has been
published by the Shanghai Literature and Art Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The books show behind-the-scenes aspects of the movie, the most
expensive production in China's film-making history.
</P>
<P>
The Opium War broke out in 1840 after the Qing-Dynasty troops
burnt a large amount of opium illegally shipped to China. The
event finally resulted in the British occupation of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The book praises the director, actors and actresses involved in
the movie for their "historical sense". 
</P>
