<HEADLINE> Uganda Faces Long Dry Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A long dry season will affect the
north and the east of Uganda, the Meteorology Department has
predicted.
</P>
<P>
The dry season will come at the beginning of July and last
up to mid September, the department said in a report signed by Bwango
Apuuli, the Commissioner for Meteorology.
</P>
<P>
The negative impact on the crops will appear in most areas of
the east and the north, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The next rain season is expected to be persisting up to the
end of this year or the start of next year. Usual rain seasons
come to Uganda twice a year from April to May and from September
to October.
</P>
<P>
The next rain season is expected to bring contrywide heavy
rains. Local meteorologist said if their prediction proved right,
Uganda likely has an opportunity for a bumper harvest. enditem

