<HEADLINE> National Clothing, Accessories Trade Fair Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Business valued at approximately
600 million yuan was handled during a national exhibition of
clothing and accessories produced by township enterprises, which
ended yesterday in Dalian, one of the country's main fashion
centers in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The turnover breaks down to 389 million yuan in trading for
domestic concerns and 210 million yuan for overseas ones.
</P>
<P>
The week long fair attracted 219,000 visits of domestic and
overseas business people. A total of 29 overseas-funded and
Sino-foreign cooperative contracts were signed, involving more
than 40 million US dollars of pledged overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Township clothing enterprises have become a driving force for
the development of the country's garment industry, accounting for
80 percent of national clothing output and exports.
</P>
<P>
And township enterprises comprise 80 percent of the country's
total number of garment factories. 
</P>
