<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic Republic of Congo has
hailed Uganda and some other African states for the support rendered
during the liberation of that country, reported the local daily
the New Vision today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Charge d'Affairs of the Congo
Embassy here at the weekend said that the leadership change had
brought renewed hope in the people of the central African country.
</P>
