<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Forestry Society Marks Its 80th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 Chinese researchers
and technicians involved in the field of forestry gathered here
today to mark the 80th anniversary of the Chinese Forestry Society.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, and other Chinese
leaders sent messages of congratulation to the meeting, which was
held in the Chinese Science and Technology Conference Hall.
</P>
<P>
The Society was founded in 1917 as one of China's earliest
non-governmental learned societies. It now has more than 70,000
members in China.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun, who spoke at today's meeting, said
that the Society's members have contributed a great deal to the
country's economic development and ecological improvement.
</P>
<P>
Forestry will continue to play an important role in China's
development in the next century, the Vice-Premier said, and there
will be a lot of room for the Society to play a role, especially
in promoting science and education. He urged various departments
to strengthen afforestation efforts in order to increase forest
coverage in the country, especially on the upper reaches of major
rivers.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Forestry Xu Youfang also addressed the meeting,
calling on members to serve the reforms and development of
forestry and to make a greater contribution to solving key
problems in forestry.
</P>
<P>
A number of foreign representatives, such as those from Japan
and Canada attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
