<HEADLINE> Art Auction in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Some 300 works of art were put up
for auctioned in the capital of southwest China's Yunnan province
on June 15 by Chengdu's Sichuan Hanya Artwork Auction Company and
the local Yunnan Artwork Auction Center.
</P>
<P>
The auction offered 250 Chinese paintings and works of
calligraphy and 68 curios from 18 antique stores in southwestern
Chinese provinces.
</P>
<P>
The items included calligraphy of the Qianlong Emperor of the
Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) and paintings by such famous modern and
contemporary painters as Qi Baishi, Fu Baoshi, and Fan Zeng.
</P>
<P>
A preview was held at the provincial museum from June 12 to
14. 
</P>
