<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The European Union summit, which began today in Amsterdam,
remains under the shadow of French-German dispute over the content
of the Stability Pact. Despite several declarations made by Paris
and Bonn to de-dramatize the situation, the chances of reaching an
agreement at the summit remain small and the summit could be
prolonged after Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
-- As French troops completed their operation to evacuate
foreigners from Brazzaville on Sunday and began withdrawing from
the country, a plane of Gabonese President Omar Bongo fetched 13
delegates of the warring factions of Congo to Libreville for
round-table peace talks today to seek a solution to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- France today began a lonely fight at the EU Amsterdam summit
to put a chapter on employment and social construction into the
monetary Stability Pact of future European single currency.
</P>
<P>
The absence of an agreement between France and Germany over the
pact predicts difficult negotiations at the summit, which will
also discuss the reform of EU institutions aimed at the
enlargement of the union to admit central and eastern European
countries. 
</P>
