<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Fixed Assets Investment Up 15 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- China invested 242.5 billion yuan
in fixed assets during the January-April period, up 15 percent
from the same period of last year, said a report by the State
Statistics Bureau (SSB).
</P>
<P>
However, growth rate was 1.3 percentage points lower than that
in the same 1996 period. The investment figure does not include
personal investments in fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
China's investment in agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry,
fisheries and water resources, standing at 6.2 billion yuan during
the four-month period, accounted for 2.5 percent of the national
total investment. This rate was 1.6 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
China's western region showed strong growth momentum during the
four months. The region saw 32 billion yuan being invested in its
fixed assets, 31.8 percent more than the same period last
year. The growth rate was 17.6 percentage points higher than that
for the eastern areas, where the economy is more developed.
</P>
<P>
The report said that investment in the real estate sector grew
at a relatively low rate. A total of 76.4 billion yuan, an
increase of just 0.3 percent on an annual basis, was invested in
real estate during the January-April period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
