<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Takes More Measures to Promote Labuan as IOFC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Acting Prime
Minister Anwar Ibrahim today announced further measures for
offshore banks to spur the growth and development of Labuan as an
International Offshore Financial Center (IOFC).
</P>
<P>
These measures include allowing offshore banks operating in
Labuan to maintain their ringgit (local currency) balances in
interest bearing external accounts to allow offshore banks greater
access to ringgit businesses as well as money market operations in
Labuan, according to the Malaysian national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening of the Labuan International Summit on
Islamic Financial Instruments" in Labuan, Anwar said offshore
banks will be allowed to trade in ringgit instruments in the
secondary market and also to purchase ringgit instruments in the
primary market using foreign currencies.
</P>
<P>
Labuan is a federal territory off the coast of Sabah, East
Malaysia, with a size of 92 square kilometers and a population of
35,000. The Malaysian Parliament passed a bill on October 1, 1990
to develop Labuan as an IOFC.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, who is also finance minister, said today that in the
area of insurance, offshore life insurance companies in Labuan
would be allowed to sell investment-linked products to high net
worth Malaysians from a date to be announced later.
</P>
<P>
Anwar said the detailed guidelines on the implementation of
these new policies would be announced by the Labuan Offshore
Financial Services Authority (LOFSA) and the central bank later.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, who launched Amanah Butler Labuan Ltd, Malaysia's first
offshore money broker in Labuan, also announced a few other
measures for the benefit of Malaysians working in the offshore
financial industry and the public sector in Labuan.
</P>
<P>
Among others, allowances and facilities enjoyed by Malaysian
residents in their jobs in Labuan such as housing provided by
employers or housing allowances, regional allowances and special
Labuan allowances would be exempted from tax to be effective from
the year of assessment 1998.
</P>
<P>
They would also be given a 50 percent reduction in Customs duty
on cars purchased in Labuan and brought to other parts of the
country after the owner had served in Labuan for a minimum period
of time, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that to increase the population of Labuan and generate
critical mass and greater economic activities, branches of
universities and institutions of higher learning would be
encouraged to be set up on the island.
</P>
<P>
The number of offshore companies has increased to 1,200 at
present, double the number achieved for the whole of first five
years, he said, adding Labuan had attracted 55 offshore banks in
seven years, most of which are among the top 200 banks in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Labuan is making great strides in insurance where
the number of insurance and insurance-related companies is
expected to increase to 30 at the end of this year compared to six
at this time last year, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970616.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
