<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets With Cape Verde Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China, said here today that
the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) wishes to strengthen exchanges
and cooperation with the Movement for Democracy of Cape Verde and
to make efforts for long-term and stable friendly relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the statement in his meeting with Mario Pereira Silva,
member of the Permanent Commission of the Political Commission of
the Cape Verde Movement for Democracy, and head of a delegation of
the Movement.
</P>
<P>
Hu said the CPC and the Chinese government treasure their
relations with Cape Verde and have always been interested in the
country's development. Although the two countries are far from
each other, they have a long history of exchanges, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We appreciate the efforts of the people of Cape Verde, under
the Movement's leadership, to maintain national stability and
unity and to develop the national economy," Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He also thanked Cape Verde for its consistent support for the
"one China" policy and China's national reunification and support
for China in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Silva thanked Hu for the meeting and the warm hospitality in
China and congratulated China on its resuming the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong. The return of Hong Kong "is a big
event in the third world and we are so excited for it," he said.
</P>
<P>
Silva also thanked China for its support in Cape Verde's
national independence and economic development. He said he hopes
the two countries and the two Parties can develop a lasting
friendly relationship to make cooperation more fruitful. He
reaffirmed Cape Verde's "one China" stance and its recognition of
Taiwan as an inseparable part of China.
</P>
<P>
Silva and his delegation came here last Thursday as guests of
the CPC. During their stay in the Chinese capital, they held talks
with Li Shuzheng, head of the International Liaison Department of
the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
They are scheduled to visit Lanzhou and Xi'an in the northwest
and Qingdao of Shandong Province in the east. 
</P>
</TEXT>
