<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Government Ban on Fishing Along Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government
has reiterated its ban on large-scale fishing along sea shores,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Vice-President Omar Ali Juma made the remarks at the weekend
when talking to Director of the Hellas Tanzania Company Joseph
Haritonides at the State House.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president said it was the government policy to retain
the shallow water areas along the sea shore for the small
fishermen.
