<HEADLINE> Chinese Pigeons Carry Letters for Foreign Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- About a hundred Chinese carrier
pigeons carried letters of invitation to the "1997 Shanghai
International Children's Culture Festival" to foreign countries
recently.
</P>
<P>
To mark the festival that is to be held August 2 to 8, the
organizing committee arranged the `Pigeon Invitation' event to
attract children worldwide to China's largest city.
</P>
<P>
Xu Dexin, a member of the committee, said that the pigeons
carry the theme of `Peace, Friendship, and the Future' and have
been sent to Japan, the United States, Thailand, Korea, Spain and
Germany where they will fly around freely.
</P>
<P>
Children who receive pigeon invitation letters will be invited
as guests and the first five to contact Shanghai will be chosen as
`Peace Angels' for the festival, Xu said, and the committee will
pay for the lucky angels' visit.  
</P>
