<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits East Iran Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.5
degrees on the open-ended Richter scale hit Iran's eastern region
of Ga'en and Birjand at 07:31 local time (04:01 GMT) today.
</P>
<P>
The Seismological Center of Tehran Geophysics Institute
registered the epicenter of the quake at 350 kilometers from
Mashhad, capital of Khorasan province.
</P>
<P>
The quake-stricken area is about 900 kilometers east of
Tehran, capital of the country.
</P>
<P>
There has been no report of damages or casualties so far.
</P>
<P>
A severe earthquake with a magnitude of 7.1 degrees hit Ga'en
and Birjand on May 10, killing 1,568 people and injuring 2,300
others. It also resulted in massive material destruction and left
thousands of citizens homeless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
