<HEADLINE> Toyota Looking for Chinese Partner To Produce Corolla </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Toyota Motor Corp. is
looking for someone to cooperate with in China to provide its
Corolla automobile with the access to the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Koji Hasegawa, Toyota board chairman who is attending the '97
Shanghai International Automobile Industry Fair, says they plan to
introduce the car to China and are negotiating with Chinese
departments. Toyota sold two million units last year.
</P>
<P>
The new Corolla would be the eighth version since the car was
first developed in 1966. It has a 1.6-liter or a 1.3-liter engine.
It is now manufactured in 15 countries, Hasegawa said.
</P>
<P>
The annual auto show is popular with Chinese auto fans and
is a showcase for international and domestic auto producers. It is
held in Beijing and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
General Motors, Ford, Mitsubishi, Volkswagen, Chrysler and
Hyundai are all represented at this year's show, which runs from
June 10 to 16.
</P>
<P>
Toyota is the world's third largest automobile maker, after the
US's General Motors and Ford. It started an engine project in
Tianjin last May, and has 24 other joint ventures that give it a
strong foothold in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
