<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldier Killed by Hezbollah Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 16 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli soldier died today
after suffering serious wounds from a roadside bombing attack
late Sunday by Lebanese guerrilla forces in south Lebanon, Israel
Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Three other Israeli soldiers were also wounded the same day
when their tank hit the roadside bomb planted by gunmen of the
fundamentalist Hezbollah, or Party of God, in the eastern sector
of the Israeli self-proclaimed Security Zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
One of the soldiers was fatally injuried, but the other three
suffered only light wounds. They were all rushed to the Rambam
Hospital in the northern Israeli city of Haifa for treatment, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday also, fighting erupted between the Israeli soldiers
and the Hezbollah gunmen in other areas in the eastern and western
sectors. Israeli gunmen returned fire in retaliation against
Hezbollah's long-range mortar attacks.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday night, one Israeli paratrooper medic was
moderately wounded in a clash in the Rehan area in the eastern
sector.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the latest clashes brought to 11 the
number of Israeli soldiers killed in south Lebanon since the
beginning of the year. During the same period, at least 25
Hezbollah members have been killed in the clashes. 
</P>
