<HEADLINE> Tourism to Stay HK's Top Earner, Official Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Tourism will remain Hong Kong's
biggest foreign exchange earner, Hong Kong Secretary for Economic
Services Stephen Ip Shu-kwan predicted.
</P>
<P>
Tourism replaced textiles and garments as Hong Kong's top
foreign exchange earning industry last year, generating 84.5
billion HK dollars (10.8 billion U.S. dollars) from 11.7 million
visitors, today's South China Morning Post quoted Ip as saying.
</P>
<P>
"There will be more and more people traveling to Hong Kong
because of the many new attractions and activities organized to
lure people to come here," Ip said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that after the handover "even more people will come to
see that the city is still a good place".
</P>
<P>
A new high is expected in the number of visitors this year --
about 12.4 million, according to the Hong Kong Tourist
Association, set up by the government in 1957 to develop the
industry.
</P>
<P>
This would raise tourism revenue to 92.8 billion HK dollars
(11.9 billion U.S. dollars), up 10 percent from last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
