<DOCNO> XIE19970616.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Cargo Handling to Be Introduced in Chittagong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The authority of Bangladesh's
largest Chittagong Port finally allowed private participation in
the cargo handling activities from June 30 within the protected
areas after the port users threatened to boycott the port
indefinitely.
</P>
<P>
The Chittagong port workers, however, decided to observe
one-hour token work abstention everyday from today, in protest
against the use of private equipment.
</P>
<P>
A formal tripartite agreement, which paved the way for private
cargo handling in the port, was signed Sunday between the port
users, port authorities and Chittagong Mayor Mohiuddin Chowdhury.
</P>
<P>
After signing the agreement, the Port Users Forum called off
the strike scheduled to begin from this morning to materialize the
demands for use of private equipment in this usually
slowly-working port.
</P>
<P>
The issue on the use of private equipment emerged from early
March this year when a shipping company brought some of its
equipment inside the port jetty for handling its cargo, which was
resisted by the port's workers.
</P>
<P>
Under the pressure of the Workers Union, the port authority
withdraw the permission of private cargo handling in late March.
</P>
<P>
The Chittagong Port Employees Coordination Committee Sunday
announced that they will also go for an indefinite work abstention
program from June 30, if private equipment is allowed to be used
in the port.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
