<HEADLINE> Iranian President Back Home After Attending D-8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani returned to Tehran on Sunday night following a two-day
visit to Turkey to attend the D-8 summit, an Iranian news agency
(IRNA) report said today.
</P>
<P>
The official IRNA reported that on the sidelines of the summit
of the Developing-8 Muslim states, Rafsanjani held separate talks
with Turkish President Sulayman Demirel, Indonesian President
Suharto, Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan and Malaysian
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Rafsanjani strongly condemned the
resolution passed last Wednesday by the U.S. House of
Representatives to remove the U.S. embassy in Israel from Tel Aviv
to Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He termed the U.S. action as a clear support of Israel and said
the entire Muslim world should oppose this decision.
</P>
<P>
The Developing-8 group comprises Turkey, Indonesia, Egypt,
Malaysia, Pakistan, Nigeria, Bangladesh and Iran. 
