<HEADLINE> AIDS Kill 4,000 Zambians Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government is concerned
with the devastation to the human resources by the AIDS as about
4,000 people die of the deadly disease in Zambia every year.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Zambian Deputy Minister of Health Nkandu
Luo at the weekend at a function of the Rotary Club of Lusaka Central.
</P>
<P>
There are also other diseases like dysentery and cholera in the
country due to a lack of clean water and environments in most
townships, according to Luo.
</P>
<P>
She said that service clubs like Rotary and NGOs play an
important role in the development of the nation and the government
is keen to develop further its relationship with service clubs and
NGOs to ensure sustainable health delivery is achieved.
</P>
<P>
Luo noted, "Even the most beautiful health policies cannot be
achieved without being implemented. The government cannot reach the
grassroots and that is where the NGOs and service clubs come in."
