<HEADLINE> 2 Million Indonesians May Carry HIV by 2000: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- More than two million Indonesians
will be carrying HIV and AIDS by the year 2000 unless the
government took preventive measures against AIDS, a senior
official said.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Sujudi said Sunday in Padang, West Sumatra,
that the number of Indonesians exposed to AIDS was closely
associated with a wider area, according to reports reaching here
today.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, he added, 30 to 40 million people in the world,
including 80 percent in Asia, would be affected with HIV and AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the ministry of health said that 18 more people had
been diagnosed with HIV/AIDS up to May 31, bringing the number of
reported cases to 545 in the country.
</P>
<P>
Among them, 413 were HIV carriers and 132 had full-blown AIDS.
 
</P>
