MEXICO CITY, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Buhe, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress, left
here for home today after his three-week visit to Trinidad and
Tobago, Bolivia and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Buhe exchanged views with leaders of the
three countries on bilateral relations and world issues of common
interest.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the three countries praised China's developments
over the past several years, reiterated their commitment to "One
China" policy and congratulated China on its resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Buhe hailed the achievements the three countries scored in
their drive to maintain political stability, develop their
national economy and improve people's living standards.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped China and the three Latin American countries
would further friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Buhe also briefed those leaders on China's economic
developments and China's construction of democracy and legal
system.
</P>
<P>
Buhe started the visit on May 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
