<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Growing Private Sector of Economy in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Since China started opening to the
outside world in late 1978, Sichuan province's privately-owned
enterprises have had 100 billion yuan in industrial output value
and 300 billion yuan in sales.
</P>
<P>
These have had annual growth of from 20 to 50 percent,
according to local sources. The province had more than 2 million
privately-owned businesses by 1996 that generated 23.96 billion
yuan in combined output value in the past year. They had 53.03
billion yuan in the total volume of business, putting Sichuan far
ahead of other parts of southwest China.
</P>
<P>
According to the same sources, the province has seen marked
increases in the number in these in the first five months of this
year.
</P>
<P>
The growth comes because of preferential policies that
encourage development of the private sector of the economy,
sources say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
