<HEADLINE> FC Porto Wins Third Consecutive Championship Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- FC Porto's 3-0 win over Gil
Vincente in the last round of Portuguese soccer championship
Sunday brought them a third consecutive championship title in
style.
</P>
<P>
Mielcarski, Sergio Conceicao and Carlos Filipe notched goals to
lift FC Porto to its seventh title in 10 years with 85 points to
Sporting's 72.
</P>
<P>
FC Porto's Mario Jardel won one more title for the club. With
30 goals Jardel is the top scorer of the league.
</P>
<P>
Despite the 2-1 loss against Boavista, Sporting's runner-up
position remained secured enabling them to play the qualifying
games for the European Champions Cup.
</P>
<P>
Three clubs placed at the bottom of the division: Espinho,
Leiria and Gil Vicente, are relegated from the first division.
</P>
