<HEADLINE> Lithuania Win Women's European Basketball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania beat Slovakia 72-62 to
win the European women's basketball championship here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The two teams played a tense battle in the final as both teams
concentrated on defence in the opening minutes. But Slovakia soon
launched a powerful offensive which put them six points ahead by
the 16th minute in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The Lithuanians then fought back and finished the first half
with a one-point edge and in the second half they stretched their
advantage.
</P>
<P>
Later in the second half, Slovakia pushed harder but failed to
find any weakness in a tight Lithuanian defence.
</P>
<P>
In the third-place playoff, the physically and tactically
superior German team scored a 86-61 victory over Hungary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
