<HEADLINE> Tauziat Wins DFS Classic Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Nathalie Tauziat of France beat
Yayuk Basuki of Indonesia 2-6, 6-2, 6-2 to win the DFS Classic at
Birmingham on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Tauziat lost five games in succession in the
first set against the Indonesian fourth seed, but turned it around
in the second set by winning five games in a row herself for a 5-0
lead.
</P>
<P>
When she broke Basuki's serve 4-2 in the final set, the
Indonesian had no reply. 
</P>
