<HEADLINE> Bolivia Stroll to Win over Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Hosts Bolivia strolled to a 2-0 win
over Peru at the Copa America soccer tournament at La Paz on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Goals by Marco Etcheverry and Julio Baldivieso gave the hosts
three points in Group B to ensure them of a quarter-final berth.
</P>
<P>
Peru have rested nearly all their regular internationals for
World Cup qualifiers and their team was virtually an under-23
squad. But, with three points from Thursday's win over Uruguay,
they could still make the last eight.
</P>
<P>
Etcheverry capped 45 minutes of Bolivian dominance by scoring
from an unmarked position on the stroke of halftime.
</P>
<P>
Baldivieso broke through the defence and rounded Miranda to
score the second five minutes after the break. 
</P>
